;; ESH-0095 minimal repro (found by the AD composition oracle, P3).
;; laplacian with a TENSOR point SIGSEGVs; (vector ...) point works.
;; Same family as the hessian repro: second-order AD ops crash on
;; HEAP_SUBTYPE_TENSOR points while first-order ops handle them.
;;
;; Run: build/eshkol-run -r tests/ad_oracle/found/esh0095_laplacian_tensor_point_sigsegv.esk
;; Expected: 2 twice. Actual: first display OK, then SIGSEGV.
(display (laplacian (lambda (v) (* (vref v 0) (vref v 0))) (vector 1.0 2.0)))
(newline)
(display (laplacian (lambda (v) (* (vref v 0) (vref v 0))) (tensor 1.0 2.0)))
(newline)
